President Barack Obama has proclaimed June 2015 as National Oceans Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of oceans, coasts, and Great Lakes to the American people, emphasizing their contribution to recreation, tourism, food supply, economy, national defense, scientific research, and innovation. The proclamation also addresses the threats to marine environments, such as climate change, carbon pollution, and illegal fishing, and the need for actions to protect and preserve these ecosystems. President Obama mentions the National Ocean Policy and the government's efforts to manage coasts and oceans, improve the ocean economy, and promote marine conservation. He also mentions his administration's actions to preserve marine reserves and calls upon Americans to take action to protect and restore oceans, coasts, and Great Lakes.